<section class="intro">
	<div class="intro_text" id="intro_text">
		<p class="lead">
			This is TheTimesCenter, designed by Renzo Piano. Discover two flexible spaces, designed to accommodate a wide variety of events: <a href="javascript:void(0)" data-target="thestage">The Stage</a>, a striking 378-seat auditorium that can also be used as a <a href="javascript:void(0)" data-target="thescreeningroom">Screening Room</a> for cinema-quality presentations; and <a href="javascript:void(0)" data-target="thehall">The Hall</a>, a customizable 5,000 square-foot banquet room and product show space. Expect the latest in digital projection, lighting and audio resources. And rely on a team of event experts, dedicated to making the impossible seem effortless. Here, in the heart of Manhattan, the possibilities of <span class="joinWords">your event are redefined.</span>
		</p>
		<h3>Extraordinary. Engaging. Effortless.</h3>
	</div>
	<!-- /.intro_text -->
	<figure class="jumbotron">
		<img src="/assets/img/home/auditorium-stage-table.jpg" width="100%" class="special" />
	</figure>
	<p style="height:0;width:0;position:absolute;bottom:40px" id="spaces"></p>
</section>
